FBIS4-14095 "drnes082_s_94012" FBIS-NES-94-082 Daily Report 28 Apr 1994 Iran Canadian Envoy Apologizes for `Inappropriate Conduct' Canadian Envoy Apologizes for `Inappropriate Conduct' NC2804080194 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network in Persian 0230 GMT 28 Apr 94 NC2804080194 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network Persian BFN [Text] Following inappropriate conduct by the Consular Section of the Canadian Embassy in Tehran toward Iranians, the Canadian ambassador in Iran was summoned to the Foreign Ministry yesterday. A protest was conveyed to him along with the necessary recommendations. In reply, Donald P. Mcdonald, the Canadian ambassador in Tehran, expressed his regret, apologized for the situation, and promised that such conduct would be prevented.
